import java.sql.*;   // Import necessary Java packages such as ResultSet, Statement and DriverManager for database connectivity & handling operations: JDBC - Java Database Connectivity API to connect with relational databases (MySQL in this case) via SQL queries are used here without using any ORM tools or frameworks
import java.util.*;  // Import necessary classes such as ArrayList from the Collection Framework, List and Iterator for handling operations related list-related functionalities: Elements at given positions can be removed/modified through iterators while maintaining order in a data structure (LinkedList) using methods like add(int index), remove(index position).
import java.security.*;  // Import necessary classes such as MessageDigest for handling operations related to secure password hashing: Secure Hash Algorithms are used here without the use of external libraries or tools, it's highly recommended that you have a strong understanding and careful implementation in your application layers (like Controller layer)
import javax.crypto.*;  // Import necessary classes such as Cipher for handling operations related to encryption/decryption: Security provided by Java Cryptography Architecture - JCA can be used here without the use of external libraries or tools, it's highly recommended that you have a strong understanding and careful implementation in your application layers (like Controller layer)
import javax.xml.*;  // Import necessary classes such as DocumentBuilderFactory for handling operations related to XML: DOM is being replaced by SAX/StAX parsing which provides more flexible options with less memory consumption, it can be used here without the use of external libraries or tools and preferable if you have a lot data in xml files.
import javax.mail.*;  // Import necessary classes such as Session for handling operations related to email: Java Mail API is being replaced by SMTP (Simple Mail Transfer Protocol) which provides more secure communication with less memory consumption, it can be used here without the use of external libraries or tools and preferable if you want a solution that handles emails in real time.
import com.fasterxml.*;  // Import necessary classes such as XStream for handling operations related to XML serialization/deserialization: SAX (Simple API for XML) can be used here without the use of external libraries or tools, it's highly recommended when working with huge data sets in xml files and if your application is multi-threaded.